en_177432_0	The Epidemiology Unit says that there is a risk of communicable deceases being spread following heavy showers experienced in many parts of the island.
en_177432_1	Director of the Unit, Doctor Samitha Ginige said that it is important to drink boiled water and consume properly cooked foods to avoid contracting such deceases.
en_177432_2	Meanwhile, 173,000 dengue patients have been reported so far this year.
en_177432_3	Although the situation was brought under control, rains experienced recently could once again increase the risk of dengue, the doctor said.
